{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0193igZdWUpW3hDPp3EYDedb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\"  xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     2→         xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     3→  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     4→\n     5→  <parent>\n     6→    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n     7→    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>\n     8→    <version>3.3.7</version>\n     9→    <relativePath/>\n    10→  </parent>\n    11→\n    12→  <groupId>example</groupId>\n    13→  <artifactId>order-boot</artifactId>\n    14→  <version>1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>\n    15→  <name>order-boot</name>\n    16→  <packaging>jar</packaging>\n    17→\n    18→  <properties>\n    19→    <java.version>17</java.version>\n    20→    <joinfaces.version>5.5.6</joinfaces.version>\n    21→    <maven.compiler.source>17</maven.compiler.source>\n    22→    <maven.compiler.target>17</maven.compiler.target>\n    23→    <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    24→  </properties>\n    25→\n    26→  <dependencyManagement>\n    27→    <dependencies>\n    28→      <dependency>\n    29→        <groupId>org.joinfaces</groupId>\n    30→        <artifactId>joinfaces-bom</artifactId>\n    31→        <version>${joinfaces.version}</version>\n    32→        <type>pom</type>\n    33→        <scope>import</scope>\n    34→      </dependency>\n    35→    </dependencies>\n    36→  </dependencyManagement>\n    37→\n    38→  <dependencies>\n    39→    <dependency>\n    40→      <groupId>org.joinfaces</groupId>\n    41→      <artifactId>primefaces-spring-boot-starter</artifactId>\n    42→    </dependency>\n    43→    <dependency>\n    44→      <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    45→      <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-data-jpa</artifactId>\n    46→    </dependency>\n    47→    <dependency>\n    48→      <groupId>com.h2database</groupId>\n    49→      <artifactId>h2</artifactId>\n    50→      <version>2.2.224</version>\n    51→      <scope>runtime</scope>\n    52→    </dependency>\n    53→    <dependency>\n    54→      <groupId>jakarta.inject</groupId>\n    55→      <artifactId>jakarta.inject-api</artifactId>\n    56→    </dependency>\n    57→  </dependencies>\n    58→\n    59→  <build>\n    60→    <plugins>\n    61→      <plugin>\n    62→        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    63→        <artifactId>spring-boot-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n    64→      </plugin>\n    65→    </plugins>\n    66→  </build>\n    67→</project>\n    68→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e5346349-b71f-448a-8248-bfaa3fb83460","uuid":"e5453e41-5bb3-48cb-841a-be96f984b669"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TF217JeVNorJN9BXXsmhuA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl python3-venv python3-full     && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     6→\n     7→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     8→\n     9→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    10→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    11→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    12→\n    13→# create venv and install\n    14→RUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    15→\n    16→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    17→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    18→\n    19→# Set working directory\n    20→WORKDIR /app\n    21→\n    22→# Copy all the assets\n    23→COPY . .\n    24→\n    25→RUN if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    26→\n    27→CMD [ \"mvn\", \"clean\", \"package\", \"spring-boot:run\" ]\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e5346349-b71f-448a-8248-bfaa3fb83460","uuid":"ba7c0b8c-304b-4933-8bfc-8154a01af230"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018Qacev2GzojnsiDGaUrFmx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→server.port=8081\n     2→\n     3→spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:testdb\n     4→spring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver\n     5→spring.datasource.username=sa\n     6→spring.datasource.password=\n     7→\n     8→spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\n     9→spring.jpa.show-sql=true\n    10→spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.format_sql=true\n    11→\n    12→spring.h2.console.enabled=true\n    13→spring.h2.console.path=/h2-console\n    14→\n    15→joinfaces.faces.PROJECT_STAGE=Development\n    16→joinfaces.primefaces.theme=saga\n    17→\n    18→logging.level.com.example.orderspring=INFO\n    19→logging.level.org.hibernate.SQL=DEBUG\n    20→logging.level.org.hibernate.type.descriptor.sql=TRACE\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e5346349-b71f-448a-8248-bfaa3fb83460","uuid":"0a5dc257-33f8-47fd-892d-9954f358d1ad"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NLBPfBbdxucwiNQPjVCH17","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring;\n     2→\n     3→import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\n     4→import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\n     5→\n     6→@SpringBootApplication\n     7→public class OrderApplication {\n     8→\n     9→    public static void main(String[] args) {\n    10→        SpringApplication.run(OrderApplication.class, args);\n    11→    }\n    12→}\n    13→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e5346349-b71f-448a-8248-bfaa3fb83460","uuid":"77eb9456-2cc5-4cbd-a349-8938bbeb61ab"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AhQgQY1aD2YDr4RF5EfF7m","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import java.io.Serializable;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Collection;\n     7→import java.util.Date;\n     8→\n     9→@Entity\n    10→@Table(name=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_CUSTOMERORDER\")\n    11→@NamedQuery(\n    12→    name=\"findAllOrders\",\n    13→    query=\"SELECT co FROM CustomerOrder co \" +\n    14→          \"ORDER BY co.orderId\"\n    15→)\n    16→public class CustomerOrder implements Serializable {\n    17→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 6582105865012174694L;\n    18→\n    19→    private Integer orderId;\n    20→    private char status;\n    21→    private Date lastUpdate;\n    22→    private int discount;\n    23→    private String shipmentInfo;\n    24→    private Collection<LineItem> lineItems = new ArrayList<>();\n    25→\n    26→    public CustomerOrder() {\n    27→        this.lastUpdate = new Date();\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    public CustomerOrder(Integer orderId, char status, int discount, \n    31→            String shipmentInfo) {\n    32→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    33→        this.status = status;\n    34→        this.discount = discount;\n    35→        this.shipmentInfo = shipmentInfo;\n    36→        this.lastUpdate = new Date();\n    37→    }\n    38→\n    39→    @Id\n    40→    public Integer getOrderId() {\n    41→        return orderId;\n    42→    }\n    43→    \n    44→    public void setOrderId(Integer orderId) {\n    45→        this.orderId = orderId;\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    public char getStatus() {\n    49→        return status;\n    50→    }\n    51→    \n    52→    public void setStatus(char status) {\n    53→        this.status = status;\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)\n    57→    public Date getLastUpdate() {\n    58→        return lastUpdate;\n    59→    }\n    60→    \n    61→    public void setLastUpdate(Date lastUpdate) {\n    62→        this.lastUpdate = lastUpdate;\n    63→    }\n    64→\n    65→    public int getDiscount() {\n    66→        return discount;\n    67→    }\n    68→    \n    69→    public void setDiscount(int discount) {\n    70→        this.discount = discount;\n    71→    }\n    72→\n    73→    public String getShipmentInfo() {\n    74→        return shipmentInfo;\n    75→    }\n    76→    \n    77→    public void setShipmentInfo(String shipmentInfo) {\n    78→        this.shipmentInfo = shipmentInfo;\n    79→    }\n    80→\n    81→    @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.ALL, mappedBy = \"customerOrder\", orphanRemoval = true)\n    82→    public Collection<LineItem> getLineItems() {\n    83→        return lineItems;\n    84→    }\n    85→    \n    86→    public void setLineItems(Collection<LineItem> lineItems) {\n    87→        this.lineItems = lineItems;\n    88→    }\n    89→\n    90→    public double calculateAmmount() {\n    91→        double amount = 0;\n    92→        for (LineItem item : getLineItems()) {\n    93→            if (item.getVendorPart() != null) {\n    94→                amount += item.getVendorPart().getPrice() * item.getQuantity();\n    95→            }\n    96→        }\n    97→        return (amount * (100 - getDiscount())) / 100.0;\n    98→    }\n    99→\n   100→    public double calculateAmount() {\n   101→        return calculateAmmount();\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→    public void addLineItem(LineItem lineItem) {\n   105→        lineItem.setCustomerOrder(this);\n   106→        this.getLineItems().add(lineItem);\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    @Transient\n   110→    public int getNextId() {\n   111→        return this.lineItems.size() + 1;\n   112→    }\n   113→\n   114→    @PrePersist\n   115→    @PreUpdate\n   116→    private void touchLastUpdate() {\n   117→        this.lastUpdate = new Date();\n   118→    }\n   119→}\n   120→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e5346349-b71f-448a-8248-bfaa3fb83460","uuid":"1c5d8a8e-d9b1-424d-88cb-8e195f173e56"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014q5VvMqRA535NSf2xgVmgT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import java.io.Serializable;\n     5→\n     6→@IdClass(LineItemKey.class)\n     7→@Entity\n     8→@Table(name=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_LINEITEM\")\n     9→@NamedQueries({\n    10→  @NamedQuery(name=\"findAllLineItems\", query=\"SELECT l FROM LineItem l\"),\n    11→  @NamedQuery(name=\"findLineItemsByOrderId\",\n    12→              query=\"SELECT l FROM LineItem l WHERE l.customerOrder.orderId = :orderId ORDER BY l.itemId\"),\n    13→  @NamedQuery(name=\"findLineItemById\",\n    14→              query=\"SELECT DISTINCT l FROM LineItem l WHERE l.itemId = :itemId AND l.customerOrder.orderId = :orderId\")\n    15→})\n    16→public class LineItem implements Serializable {\n    17→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 3229188813505619743L;\n    18→\n    19→    private int itemId;\n    20→    private int quantity;\n    21→    private VendorPart vendorPart;\n    22→    private CustomerOrder customerOrder;\n    23→\n    24→    public LineItem() { }\n    25→\n    26→    public LineItem(CustomerOrder order, int quantity, VendorPart vendorPart) {\n    27→        this.customerOrder = order;\n    28→        this.itemId = order.getNextId();\n    29→        this.quantity = quantity;\n    30→        this.vendorPart = vendorPart;\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    @Id\n    34→    public int getItemId() { return itemId; }\n    35→    public void setItemId(int itemId) { this.itemId = itemId; }\n    36→\n    37→    public int getQuantity() { return quantity; }\n    38→    public void setQuantity(int quantity) { this.quantity = quantity; }\n    39→\n    40→    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    41→    @JoinColumn(name=\"VENDORPARTNUMBER\")\n    42→    public VendorPart getVendorPart() { return vendorPart; }\n    43→    public void setVendorPart(VendorPart vendorPart) { this.vendorPart = vendorPart; }\n    44→\n    45→    @Id\n    46→    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    47→    @JoinColumn(name=\"ORDERID\")\n    48→    public CustomerOrder getCustomerOrder() { return customerOrder; }\n    49→    public void setCustomerOrder(CustomerOrder customerOrder) { this.customerOrder = customerOrder; }\n    50→}\n    51→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e5346349-b71f-448a-8248-bfaa3fb83460","uuid":"b47eee3f-b6fc-4711-a8a7-fc5674db0e0b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01L9XPzFFJJ6c1eSChCk8BDf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→\n     5→public final class LineItemKey implements Serializable {\n     6→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1562260205094677677L;\n     7→    private Integer customerOrder;\n     8→    private int itemId;\n     9→\n    10→    public LineItemKey() {\n    11→    }\n    12→\n    13→    public LineItemKey(Integer order, int itemId) {\n    14→        this.setCustomerOrder(order);\n    15→        this.setItemId(itemId);\n    16→    }\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public int hashCode() {\n    20→        return ((this.getCustomerOrder() == null\n    21→                ? 0 : this.getCustomerOrder().hashCode())\n    22→                ^ ((int) this.getItemId()));\n    23→    }\n    24→\n    25→    @Override\n    26→    public boolean equals(Object otherOb) {\n    27→        if (this == otherOb) {\n    28→            return true;\n    29→        }\n    30→        if (!(otherOb instanceof LineItemKey)) {\n    31→            return false;\n    32→        }\n    33→        LineItemKey other = (LineItemKey) otherOb;\n    34→        return ((this.getCustomerOrder() == null\n    35→                ? other.getCustomerOrder() == null : this.getCustomerOrder()\n    36→                .equals(other.getCustomerOrder()))\n    37→                && (this.getItemId() == other.getItemId()));\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    @Override\n    41→    public String toString() {\n    42→        return \"\" + getCustomerOrder() + \"-\" + getItemId();\n    43→    }\n    44→\n    45→    public Integer getCustomerOrder() {\n    46→        return customerOrder;\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    public void setCustomerOrder(Integer order) {\n    50→        this.customerOrder = order;\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    public int getItemId() {\n    54→        return itemId;\n    55→    }\n    56→\n    57→    public void setItemId(int itemId) {\n    58→        this.itemId = itemId;\n    59→    }\n    60→}\n    61→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e5346349-b71f-448a-8248-bfaa3fb83460","uuid":"d44234ec-e859-4e9d-9ac9-bb0781f2a07f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Ha9xWqVzmmiwfo7fyY5aHR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package com.example.orderspring.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import java.io.Serializable;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Date;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→\n     9→@IdClass(PartKey.class)\n    10→@Entity\n    11→@Table(name=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_PART\")\n    12→@SecondaryTable(name=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_PART_DETAIL\", pkJoinColumns={\n    13→   @PrimaryKeyJoinColumn(name=\"PARTNUMBER\", referencedColumnName=\"PARTNUMBER\"),\n    14→   @PrimaryKeyJoinColumn(name=\"REVISION\", referencedColumnName=\"REVISION\")\n    15→})\n    16→@NamedQuery(name=\"findAllParts\",\n    17→    query=\"SELECT p FROM Part p ORDER BY p.partNumber\")\n    18→public class Part implements Serializable {\n    19→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -3082087016342644227L;\n    20→\n    21→    private String partNumber;\n    22→    private int revision;\n    23→    private String description;\n    24→    private Date revisionDate;\n    25→    private Serializable drawing;\n    26→    private String specification;\n    27→    private Part bomPart;\n    28→    private List<Part> parts = new ArrayList<>();\n    29→    private VendorPart vendorPart;\n    30→\n    31→    public Part() {}\n    32→\n    33→    public Part(String partNumber, int revision, String description,\n    34→                Date revisionDate, String specification, Serializable drawing) {\n    35→        this.partNumber = partNumber;\n    36→        this.revision = revision;\n    37→        this.description = description;\n    38→        this.revisionDate = revisionDate;\n    39→        this.specification = specification;\n    40→        this.drawing = drawing;\n    41→    }\n    42→\n    43→    @Id @Column(nullable=false)\n    44→    public String getPartNumber() { return partNumber; }\n    45→    public void setPartNumber(String partNumber) { this.partNumber = partNumber; }\n    46→\n    47→    @Id @Column(nullable=false)\n    48→    public int getRevision() { return revision; }\n    49→    public void setRevision(int revision) { this.revision = revision; }\n    50→\n    51→    public String getDescription() { return description; }\n    52→    public void setDescription(String description) { this.description = description; }\n    53→\n    54→    @Temporal(TemporalType.DATE)\n    55→    public Date getRevisionDate() { return revisionDate; }\n    56→    public void setRevisionDate(Date revisionDate) { this.revisionDate = revisionDate; }\n    57→\n    58→    @Lob @Basic(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    59→    @Column(table=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_PART_DETAIL\")\n    60→    public Serializable getDrawing() { return drawing; }\n    61→    public void setDrawing(Serializable drawing) { this.drawing = drawing; }\n    62→\n    63→    @Lob @Basic(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    64→    @Column(table=\"PERSISTENCE_ORDER_PART_DETAIL\")\n    65→    public String getSpecification() { return specification; }\n    66→    public void setSpecification(String specification) { this.specification = specification; }\n    67→\n    68→    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    69→    @JoinColumns({\n    70→        @JoinColumn(name=\"BOMPARTNUMBER\", referencedColumnName=\"PARTNUMBER\"),\n    71→        @JoinColumn(name=\"BOMREVISION\", referencedColumnName=\"REVISION\")\n    72→    })\n    73→    public Part getBomPart() { return bomPart; }\n    74→    public void setBomPart(Part bomPart) { this.bomPart = bomPart; }\n    75→\n    76→    @OneToMany(mappedBy=\"bomPart\")\n    77→    public List<Part> getParts() { return parts; }\n    78→    public void setParts(List<Part> parts) { this.parts = parts; }\n    79→\n    80→    @OneToOne(mappedBy=\"part\", fetch = FetchType.LAZY)\n    81→    public VendorPart getVendorPart() { return vendorPart; }\n    82→    public void setVendorPart(VendorPart vendorPart) { this.vendorPart = vendorPart; }\n    83→}\n    84→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e5346349-b71f-448a-8248-bfaa3fb83460","uuid":"715bbf30-93f5-459c-ba81-30f84a97707c"}
